// Game: Postretro
// Format: Standard
// DEMO MAP — M10 entity health + damage runtime AND M10 enemy AI / pathfinding.
// One large open arena (top-down; x is east, y is north; interior x 0..1024,
// y 0..512, floor z=0, ceiling z=128). Three free-standing full-height pillars
// sit along the centerline between the player (west) and the enemy (east), so the
// straight line is blocked, but there is wide open floor (>=160 units) on BOTH
// sides of every pillar -- the agent rounds them in the open, never wedges.
// Legend: # = wall/pillar, . = floor, P = player_spawn, E = reference_enemy, d = dummy.
//   y=512  ################################################################
//          #..............................................................#
//          #..............................................................#
//          #..........##..........##..........##..........................#
//          #...P..d.d..##....d.....##..........##.....................E....#
//          #...........##..........##..........##.........................#
//          #..............................................................#
//          #..............................................................#
//   y=0    ################################################################
//          x=0    256 320   480 544   704 768                          1024
// Pillars (free-standing, full-height z[0,128]):
//   WEST   x[256,320] y[200,296]
//   CENTER x[480,544] y[208,304]  -- blocks the straight P->E line (both at y=256)
//   EAST   x[704,768] y[216,312]
// Every gap (pillar->wall, pillar->pillar) is >=160 units wide -- no narrow
// passages, no S-turns, no capsule-wedging pockets. The agent detours north or
// south of the center pillar (~208 units clear each way) to reach the player.
// Toggle the nav overlay in-game with Alt+Shift+N.
// Compile: cargo run -p postretro-level-compiler -- content/dev/maps/combat-demo.map -o content/dev/maps/combat-demo.prl
// Run:     cargo run -p postretro -- content/dev/maps/combat-demo.prl
// See content/dev/maps/combat-demo.README.md for what to look for.
// entity 0
{
"classname" "worldspawn"
"initialGravity" "-9.81"
"wad" ""
"data_script" "../scripts/combat-demo-reaction.ts"
"_tb_mod" "dev"
